we need to return the number of trailing zeroes in the factorial

brute force :-
  find the factorial and keep dividing by 10 and keep a count
 constraints for n are too high n = 10^4
  optimal approach

2 and 5 make up 10 we need to count the number of 5's from n to 1 to know how many 0's will be made

code:-
class Solution {
public:
    int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int ans = 0;

        while (n > 0) {
            n /= 5;
            ans += n;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
